OL,4,Cbaby boy in Merseyside
OL,6,FDoctors subsequently discovered that
OL,7,FMiguel had sustained bruising on the
OL,8,Fleft side of his head, while a CT scan
OL,9,Ffound a fissure to his skull and
OL,10,Fbleeding on the brain, in addition to
OL,11,Ffractures to his right collarbone,
OL,12,Fleft upper arm and left shin. These
OL,13,Fbroken bones were said to have been of
OL,14,Fvarying age, with Mr Wright saying:
OL,15,F"The inevitable conclusion to be drawn
OL,16,Ffrom the injuries was that Miguel had
OL,17,Fbeen subjected to a course of conduct
OL,18,Fin which serious and obvious injuries
OL,19,Fhad been sustained."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/21
