OL,6,FMr Wright added: "The evidence
OL,7,Fdemonstrates that the injuries to
OL,8,FMiguel's ribs were of varying ages.
OL,9,FSome had been inflicted in advance of
OL,10,Fthe 24th of November. Any fractures
OL,11,Flater found were, in the opinion of
OL,12,Fthe Home Office forensic pathologist,
OL,13,Fnot consistent with CPR. Each of the
OL,14,Finjuries found, whether fatal or non-
OL,15,Ffatal, were, in his professional
OL,16,Fopinion, non-accidental in origin.
